        {
          "id": "GxhS1X6JDRt2x1Ra",
          "title": "Text 2",
          "content": {
            "type": "Text",
            "format": "html",
            "text": [
              "<p>Amber uses the board to the left to claim that Tate is “in the red” 2 dollars or has –2 dollars. </p><p>She writes +4 + –6 = –2 </p><p></p>"
            ]
          }
        }
      ],
      {
        "id": "N9M8XO6bWkJwByER",
        "title": "Text 3",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>Why do you think she concludes that +4 + –6 = –2? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "hVmvoCAT2hQrQaLr",
        "title": "Text 6",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Possible answer: If you lose 6 dollars and you only gain 4 dollars back, then your total change will be a loss of 2 dollars. This is modeled in the number sentence -6 + 4 = -2.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "HvKA9G7jz5Dud1fT",
        "title": "Text 4",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>What is another way to show a total value of –2 on the chip board? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "Op57dhKxdZhKOaHa",
        "title": "Text 7",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Many possible answers: You could have: </p><ul><li>two red chips on the board with no black chips,</li><li>1 black chip and 3 red chips,</li><li>2 black chips and 4 red chips,</li><li>3 black chips and 5 red chips, etc.</li></ul><p>Any value of black chips could work, as long as you have 2 extra red chips.</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "EMhJtxQGBEY9Co8A",
        "title": "Text 5",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>Suppose she changes the board by adding one red chip and one black chip. How much does this change the total value? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "Kjw1MP3IMxFkxpcc",
        "title": "Text 8",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>It does not change the total value at all. Adding 1 black chip and 1 red chip represents adding 1 + -1, which equals zero.</p>"
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
